# A cold build runs cmake; after dropping the build dir and reloading (clears task memoisation, the action cache
# persists on disk), the rebuild must be a cache hit - cmake does not rerun and the archive is restored.
> snxVendoredArtefacts
> assertBuilt
> removeBuild
> reload
> snxVendoredArtefacts
> assertCached

# Editing a vendored source changes its content hash, so the cache key changes and the next build is a miss -
# cmake reruns and the build dir reappears.
$ copy-file changes/answer.c vendor/answer/answer.c
> reload
> snxVendoredArtefacts
> assertBuilt
